  "text": "· A w is the chamber wall correction factor [CITATION_1] to account for scattering and attenuation in the wall of the ionization chamber. A w is determined using a formula A w ≈ 1 -γt, where γ is the attenuation and scattering fraction per wall thickness (cm 2 /g) and taken as 0.0277 and t is the total thickness (g/cm 2 ) of wall material.",
